{
    "_metadata": {
      "description": "Interactive Brokers to Bloomberg exchange code mapper for equities and ETFs",
      "last_updated": "2026-04-20",
      "usage_notes": [
        "Use 'bbg_code' as the 2-letter Bloomberg exchange suffix (e.g. 'UW' for AAPL UW Equity).",
        "Use 'bbg_composite' when you want the country-level composite feed instead of a specific venue.",
        "For Bloomberg PORT uploads, prefer specific 'bbg_code' over composite unless the position is genuinely cross-listed and you don't care which venue.",
        "If an IB code is missing here, ISIN + CURRENCY alone is almost always sufficient for Bloomberg to resolve the security.",
        "SMART is IB's router, not an exchange — resolve the actual listing exchange before mapping.",
        "Where IB uses multiple codes for the same venue (e.g. IBIS/IBIS2 both = XETRA), all variants map to the same Bloomberg code."
      ]
    },
  
